* DevOps Project Architecture: It shows how code moves from development to production using automation, CI/CD, monitoring, and Infrastructure Management.

*DevOps Project Flow (Step-by-Step)
1. Code Development (Developer Stage)
-> Developer writes code using an IDE (VS Code, IntelliJ, Eclipse, etc.).
-> Code is pushed to Git (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket).
Command: Developer → GitHub/GitLab

2. Continuous Integration (CI Stage)
-> CI Tool (Jenkins/GitHub Actions/GitLab CI) detects code changes.
   Steps performed: 
   *Code checkout
   *Build (Maven/Gradle/npm)
   *Unit Tests (JUnit, Mocha, Jest)
   *Static Code Analysis (SonarQube)
   *Security Scan (Snyk, Trivy)
Command: GitHub → Jenkins → Build + Test + SonarQube

3. Artifact Management
-> Build output (JAR, WAR, Docker Image, npm package) is stored in an Artifact Repository.
   Example: Nexus, Artifactory, AWS S3, DockerHub
Command: Jenkins → Nexus / Artifactory / DockerHub

4. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
-> Terraform / Ansible provisions servers, databases, and load balancers on AWS, Azure, or GCP.
-> Ensures reproducible environments (Dev → QA → Prod).
Command: Terraform → AWS Cloud (EC2, S3, RDS, EKS)

5. Continuous Deployment (CD Stage)
-> Jenkins (or ArgoCD, Spinnaker) deploys artifacts to servers or Kubernetes clusters.
->Deployment strategies:
  Rolling Update
  Blue-Green Deployment
  Canary Release
Commands: Jenkins → Docker → Kubernetes (EKS, AKS, GKE)

6. Containerization & Orchestration
-> Docker packages the app with dependencies.
-> Kubernetes manages scaling, load balancing, and auto-healing.
Commands: App → Docker Container → Kubernetes Pods

7. Monitoring & Logging
-> Prometheus + Grafana → Metrics (CPU, Memory, Response Time).
->ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana) → Logs.
->Alerting → Slack, Email, PagerDuty.
Command: App → Logs & Metrics → Grafana / ELK

8. Feedback Loop
-> Monitoring alerts developers about issues.
-> Developers fix bugs, push changes → Cycle repeats.
Command: Grafana/ELK → Developers → GitHub → Jenkins

Full DevOps Flow:
Developer → GitHub → Jenkins (CI/CD) → SonarQube → Nexus/DockerHub → Terraform/Ansible → Docker → Kubernetes → Prometheus/Grafana → Feedback → Developer
